FBIS3-10519 "drlat046_b_94005" FBIS-LAT-94-046 Document Type:Daily Report 9 Mar 1994 Haiti Sansaricq Senate Office Asks Employees To Stay Home FL0803230494 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 GMT 8 Mar 94 FL0803230494 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio Language: French Article Type:BFN [Text] The quaestorship of the Senate of the Republic offers congratulations to staff members and advises that in view of the tense situation developing within the administration since the return from abroad of the members of the office dismissed by resolution dated 4 February, it was decided to ask the staff to remain at home until further notice to allow the senators to settle their dispute. This communique is signed by Dr. Osny Eugene, senator of the Republic and quaestor of the Senate office presided over by Bernard Sansaricq.
